{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Generate Tests from Codebase",
  "description": "Scans the app's source code (Compose, SwiftUI, XML layouts), identifies screens, interactive elements, and user flows, then generates reusable YAML test scripts in e2e-tests/ folder with cross-platform support.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Scan the mobile app source code in this workspace. ALSO check if prompt/ folder exists — if it does, read ALL .md files in prompt/ as additional context (test flow hints, credentials, special instructions, business logic). Use this context to understand the app's flows and generate better test scripts. Find all UI source files — look for: Kotlin Compose (*.kt with @Composable), SwiftUI (*.swift with View protocol/body), XML layouts (res/layout/*.xml), UIKit storyboards/xibs. For each screen found: 1) Identify all interactive elements (TextField, Button, Checkbox, Toggle, etc.) with their accessibility labels — for Compose: contentDescription/testTag; for SwiftUI: accessibilityIdentifier/accessibilityLabel; for XML: android:contentDescription. 2) Identify user flows (what happens on tap, state changes, navigation). Use prompt/*.md context to determine correct flow order, test data, and expected behaviors. 3) Determine platform based on source language — Kotlin/XML → android; Swift → ios; if both exist → [android, ios]. 4) Generate test scripts with QUALITY OVER QUANTITY mindset. PRIORITIZE: critical user flows (login, main actions, payments), error states users actually encounter, and state transitions that could break. AVOID: redundant tests that verify the same thing in slightly different ways, trivial tests (button exists, text is visible), tests that overlap significantly with other tests. Each test case must be UNIQUE and test something MEANINGFULLY DIFFERENT. If two test cases would exercise the same code path, keep only the more comprehensive one. Aim for 2-3 high-value test cases per feature rather than 5 low-value ones. Each test case must have detailed numbered steps and SPECIFIC expected results. 5) Save YAML test scripts in e2e-tests/ folder following the schema in the generate-from-codebase steering file. Set the platform field correctly per script. Order test scripts by flow (based on prompt context if available). 6) Generate e2e-tests/coverage.yaml listing all elements found and which are covered. 7) Read e2e-tests/version.yaml — if exists, increment version by 1; if not, set version to 1. Save updated version.yaml. Output a summary of how many screens found, elements identified, platforms detected, prompt files read, total test cases generated."
  }
}